  "text": "Ribeiro et al. [CITATION_1] strive to test the sustainability of a retailing strategy so-called ugly business model in which the waste from fresh fruits and vegetables that are not sold through the conventional distribution channels, due to the appearance of these products, is minimized. According to their results, this project, in addition to the economic benefits, has had social benefits (i.e., \"increasing waste awareness and healthy food consumption and community engagement in reduction of the waste\", etc.) and environmental benefits (i.e., \"prevent food wastes and climate change mitigation benefits\").",
